            "body": "> I know it has been mentioned in `:h vim_diff`, but I think that file is kinda long,\n\nIt's right at the top:\n\n    Nvim differs from Vim in many ways, although editor and Vimscript (not Vim9script)\n\n> Just add a few lines to `:h nvim-from-vim` saying something like\n\nNo, that is much too long. `:help nvim` is supposed to be essential, and high-signal, for getting started. Explication is in `:help vim-diff`.\n\n> Also it doesn't have a seperate tag for `vim9script`\n\nI'll add a tag \n\n",
